              "content": "# Verify Settlement Calldata\n\nVerify that hex-encoded calldata matches expected parameters via round-trip encode → decode → re-encode comparison.\n\n**User argument**: $ARGUMENTS (calldata hex string starting with `0x`, or \"help\")\n\nIf the argument is \"help\" or empty, explain the verification workflow. If a calldata hex is provided, run the full verification pipeline and output a match/mismatch report.\n\n---\n\n## Verification Strategy\n\nThe complete verification pipeline:\n\n```\ncalldata → reconstructFromCalldata() → { request, response, interactions }\n         → buildSettleCalldata(request, response, { interactions })\n         → re-encoded calldata\n         → byte-by-byte comparison with original\n```\n\nIf the round-trip produces identical calldata, the encoding is verified correct.\n\n---\n\n## Step-by-Step Verification\n\n### Step 1: Decode and Reconstruct\n\n```typescript\nimport {\n  reconstructFromCalldata,\n  buildSettleCalldata,\n  decodeSettleCalldata,\n} from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-solver';\n\nconst originalCalldata = '0x...';  // the calldata to verify\n\n// Reconstruct API-level objects\nconst { request, response, interactions } = reconstructFromCalldata(originalCalldata);\n```\n\n### Step 2: Re-Encode\n\n```typescript\n// Re-encode with the same settings (useComputedPrices=true is the default)\nconst reEncoded = buildSettleCalldata(request, response, {\n  interactions,\n  useComputedPrices: true,\n});\n```\n\n### Step 3: Compare Calldata\n\n```typescript\nconst match = originalCalldata.toLowerCase() === reEncoded.calldata.toLowerCase();\nconsole.log('Round-trip match:', match ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL');\n```\n\n---\n\n## Field-Level Comparison\n\nWhen the byte-by-byte check fails, perform field-level comparison to identify exactly which fields differ:\n\n```typescript\nconst original = decodeSettleCalldata(originalCalldata);\nconst rebuilt = decodeSettleCalldata(reEncoded.calldata);\n\nconst report: string[] = [];\n\n// 1. settleId\nif (original.settleId !== rebuilt.settleId) {\n  report.push(`settleId: ${original.settleId} !== ${rebuilt.settleId}`);\n}\n\n// 2. tokens (address comparison must be case-insensitive)\nif (original.tokens.length !== rebuilt.tokens.length) {\n  report.push(`tokens.length: ${original.tokens.length} !== ${rebuilt.tokens.length}`);\n} else {\n  for (let i = 0; i \u003c original.tokens.length; i++) {\n    if (original.tokens[i].toLowerCase() !== rebuilt.tokens[i].toLowerCase()) {\n      report.push(`tokens[${i}]: ${original.tokens[i]} !== ${rebuilt.tokens[i]}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// 3. clearingPrices\nif (original.clearingPrices.length !== rebuilt.clearingPrices.length) {\n  report.push(`clearingPrices.length: ${original.clearingPrices.length} !== ${rebuilt.clearingPrices.length}`);\n} else {\n  for (let i = 0; i \u003c original.clearingPrices.length; i++) {\n    if (original.clearingPrices[i] !== rebuilt.clearingPrices[i]) {\n      report.push(`clearingPrices[${i}]: ${original.clearingPrices[i]} !== ${rebuilt.clearingPrices[i]}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// 4. trades\nif (original.trades.length !== rebuilt.trades.length) {\n  report.push(`trades.length: ${original.trades.length} !== ${rebuilt.trades.length}`);\n} else {\n  for (let i = 0; i \u003c original.trades.length; i++) {\n    const ot = original.trades[i];\n    const rt = rebuilt.trades[i];\n\n    if (ot.fromTokenAddressIndex !== rt.fromTokenAddressIndex)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].fromTokenAddressIndex: ${ot.fromTokenAddressIndex} !== ${rt.fromTokenAddressIndex}`);\n    if (ot.toTokenAddressIndex !== rt.toTokenAddressIndex)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].toTokenAddressIndex: ${ot.toTokenAddressIndex} !== ${rt.toTokenAddressIndex}`);\n    if (ot.owner.toLowerCase() !== rt.owner.toLowerCase())\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].owner: ${ot.owner} !== ${rt.owner}`);\n    if (ot.receiver.toLowerCase() !== rt.receiver.toLowerCase())\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].receiver: ${ot.receiver} !== ${rt.receiver}`);\n    if (ot.fromTokenAmount !== rt.fromTokenAmount)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].fromTokenAmount: ${ot.fromTokenAmount} !== ${rt.fromTokenAmount}`);\n    if (ot.toTokenAmount !== rt.toTokenAmount)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].toTokenAmount: ${ot.toTokenAmount} !== ${rt.toTokenAmount}`);\n    if (ot.validTo !== rt.validTo)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].validTo: ${ot.validTo} !== ${rt.validTo}`);\n    if (ot.appData !== rt.appData)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].appData: ${ot.appData} !== ${rt.appData}`);\n    if (ot.flags !== rt.flags)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].flags: ${ot.flags} !== ${rt.flags}`);\n    if (ot.executedAmount !== rt.executedAmount)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].executedAmount: ${ot.executedAmount} !== ${rt.executedAmount}`);\n    if (ot.signature !== rt.signature)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].signature: ${ot.signature} !== ${rt.signature}`);\n\n    // Commission infos\n    if (ot.commissionInfos.length !== rt.commissionInfos.length) {\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].commissionInfos.length: ${ot.commissionInfos.length} !== ${rt.commissionInfos.length}`);\n    } else {\n      for (let j = 0; j \u003c ot.commissionInfos.length; j++) {\n        const oc = ot.commissionInfos[j];\n        const rc = rt.commissionInfos[j];\n        if (oc.feePercent !== rc.feePercent)\n          report.push(`trades[${i}].commissionInfos[${j}].feePercent: ${oc.feePercent} !== ${rc.feePercent}`);\n        if (oc.referrerWalletAddress.toLowerCase() !== rc.referrerWalletAddress.toLowerCase())\n          report.push(`trades[${i}].commissionInfos[${j}].referrerWalletAddress mismatch`);\n        if (oc.flag !== rc.flag)\n          report.push(`trades[${i}].commissionInfos[${j}].flag: ${oc.flag} !== ${rc.flag}`);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Solver fee info\n    if (ot.solverFeeInfo.feePercent !== rt.solverFeeInfo.feePercent)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].solverFeeInfo.feePercent: ${ot.solverFeeInfo.feePercent} !== ${rt.solverFeeInfo.feePercent}`);\n    if (ot.solverFeeInfo.solverAddr.toLowerCase() !== rt.solverFeeInfo.solverAddr.toLowerCase())\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].solverFeeInfo.solverAddr mismatch`);\n    if (ot.solverFeeInfo.flag !== rt.solverFeeInfo.flag)\n      report.push(`trades[${i}].solverFeeInfo.flag: ${ot.solverFeeInfo.flag} !== ${rt.solverFeeInfo.flag}`);\n  }\n}\n\n// 5. interactions\nfor (let phase = 0; phase \u003c 3; phase++) {\n  const op = original.interactions[phase];\n  const rp = rebuilt.interactions[phase];\n  if (op.length !== rp.length) {\n    report.push(`interactions[${phase}].length: ${op.length} !== ${rp.length}`);\n  } else {\n    for (let j = 0; j \u003c op.length; j++) {\n      if (op[j].target.toLowerCase() !== rp[j].target.toLowerCase())\n        report.push(`interactions[${phase}][${j}].target mismatch`);\n      if (op[j].value !== rp[j].value)\n        report.push(`interactions[${phase}][${j}].value: ${op[j].value} !== ${rp[j].value}`);\n      if (op[j].callData !== rp[j].callData)\n        report.push(`interactions[${phase}][${j}].callData mismatch`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// 6. surplusFeeInfo\nif (original.surplusFeeInfo.feePercent !== rebuilt.surplusFeeInfo.feePercent)\n  report.push(`surplusFeeInfo.feePercent: ${original.surplusFeeInfo.feePercent} !== ${rebuilt.surplusFeeInfo.feePercent}`);\nif (original.surplusFeeInfo.trimReceiver.toLowerCase() !== rebuilt.surplusFeeInfo.trimReceiver.toLowerCase())\n  report.push(`surplusFeeInfo.trimReceiver mismatch`);\nif (original.surplusFeeInfo.flag !== rebuilt.surplusFeeInfo.flag)\n  report.push(`surplusFeeInfo.flag: ${original.surplusFeeInfo.flag} !== ${rebuilt.surplusFeeInfo.flag}`);\n\n// === Output Report ===\nif (report.length === 0) {\n  console.log('VERIFICATION PASSED: All fields match');\n} else {\n  console.log(`VERIFICATION FAILED: ${report.length} mismatches found`);\n  for (const line of report) {\n    console.log(`  - ${line}`);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Common Mismatch Causes\n\n| Mismatch Field | Likely Cause | Resolution |\n|----------------|-------------|------------|\n| `clearingPrices` | Original used `useComputedPrices=false` | Re-encode with `useComputedPrices=false` |\n| `tokens` addresses | Checksum vs lowercase | Compare with `.toLowerCase()` |\n| `executedAmount` | Fee rounding differences | Check fee direction and precision |\n| `trades` order | Different sort order | SDK always sorts by `toTokenAddressIndex` ascending |\n| `receiver` | `address(0)` vs actual address | `address(0)` means receiver === owner |\n| `interactions` | Missing or different calldata | Interactions must be passed explicitly |\n\n---\n\n## Complete Verification Script\n\n```typescript\nimport {\n  reconstructFromCalldata,\n  buildSettleCalldata,\n  decodeSettleCalldata,\n} from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-solver';\n\nfunction verifyCalldata(calldata: string): void {\n  console.log('=== Calldata Verification ===\\n');\n  console.log(`Input length: ${calldata.length} chars (${(calldata.length - 2) / 2} bytes)\\n`);\n\n  // Step 1: Reconstruct\n  const { request, response, interactions } = reconstructFromCalldata(calldata);\n  console.log(`Reconstructed: auctionId=${request.auctionId}, orders=${request.orders.length}`);\n\n  // Step 2: Re-encode\n  const reEncoded = buildSettleCalldata(request, response, {\n    interactions,\n    useComputedPrices: true,\n  });\n\n  // Step 3: Byte-level comparison\n  const bytesMatch = calldata.toLowerCase() === reEncoded.calldata.toLowerCase();\n  console.log(`\\nByte-level match: ${bytesMatch ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL'}`);\n\n  if (!bytesMatch) {\n    // Step 4: Field-level diff\n    const original = decodeSettleCalldata(calldata);\n    const rebuilt = decodeSettleCalldata(reEncoded.calldata);\n\n    console.log('\\nField-level comparison:');\n    console.log(`  settleId: ${original.settleId === rebuilt.settleId ? 'MATCH' : 'MISMATCH'}`);\n    console.log(`  tokens: ${original.tokens.length === rebuilt.tokens.length ? 'MATCH' : 'MISMATCH'} (${original.tokens.length} items)`);\n    console.log(`  clearingPrices: ${original.clearingPrices.every((p, i) =\u003e p === rebuilt.clearingPrices[i]) ? 'MATCH' : 'MISMATCH'}`);\n    console.log(`  trades: ${original.trades.length === rebuilt.trades.length ? 'MATCH' : 'MISMATCH'} (${original.trades.length} items)`);\n    console.log(`  surplusFeeInfo: ${original.surplusFeeInfo.feePercent === rebuilt.surplusFeeInfo.feePercent ? 'MATCH' : 'MISMATCH'}`);\n\n    // Show first byte difference position\n    const a = calldata.toLowerCase();\n    const b = reEncoded.calldata.toLowerCase();\n    for (let i = 0; i \u003c Math.max(a.length, b.length); i++) {\n      if (a[i] !== b[i]) {\n        console.log(`\\nFirst difference at byte position ${Math.floor((i - 2) / 2)}: '${a.slice(i, i + 8)}...' vs '${b.slice(i, i + 8)}...'`);\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage:\nverifyCalldata('0x...');\n```\n\n---\n\n## Build Commands Reference\n\n```bash\npnpm install                  # Install dependencies\npnpm build                    # Build all packages\npnpm typecheck                # Type-check all packages\npnpm test                     # Run all tests (includes round-trip tests)\n```\n",
